<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB03712</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT DECLARING THE EXISTENCE OF A TRAFFIC AND CONGESTION CRISIS AND GRANTING PRESIDENT RODRIGO ROA DUTERTE, EMERGENCY POWERS TO ADDRESS ITS CAUSES AND CONSEQUENCES, ADOPTING A NATIONAL POLICY AND A DECONGESTION AND TRANSPORTATION REFORM PLAN IN CONNECTION THEREWITH AND AUTHORIZING HIM, WITHIN A PERIOD OF THREE YEARS AND SUBJECT TO RESTRICTIONS, TO IMPLEMENT RULES AND REGULATIONS NECESSARY AND PROPER TO CARRY OUT SUCH POWERS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Traffic And Congestion Crisis Act Of 2016</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Declares a State policy to address the crisis – its causes and consequences – in consonance with the constitutional directive to promote social justice in all phases of national development.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SALCEDA, JOEY SARTE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-09-21</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Economic</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Batocabe (059 2017-01-18)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Scheduled for meeting/hearing on 2017-05-10</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Approved by the Committee on Appropriations on 2017-05-10</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Substitute Bill to House Bill Nos. 3, 38, 554, 1315, 1666, 3048, 3162, 3314, 3442, 3617, 3712, 3716, 4334, 4699 and HR No. 119 was approved with amendments.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB06425</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRANSPORTATION ON 2016-